The verdict is not valid, the defendant’s appeal is due to be heard by the court in December.
Tymoshenko refers to the verdict as a political revenge of the regime, suspicion of the court's interest has also triggered a trial in the West.
The proposal to remove paragraph 365 from the criminal code, on the basis of which the prime minister was convicted, supported 147 members in the vote.
It required 226 votes to be cast.
