The diet of an obese child: breakfast and dinner
More than a third of 9 to 13-year-olds have problems with overweight, with 9 percent of schoolchildren overweight and 5 percent of obese children.
Obese children usually come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to a recent study.
Again, it shows how important the environment in which he grows and the patterns in which he is surrounded is for the healthy development of man.
For example, on the tables of obese children, cucumbers appear up to half more often than in families of normal weight children.
The roasted fries had to dinner the day before the research associated with an educational event called Obesity is no coincidence more than 19 percent of obese.
It is also not a habit to play sports in fat families, which is true for most families of today's schoolchildren - only 15 percent of children answered that their parents find time for active exercise at least once a week.
A survey of 900 children.
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and was attended by almost 900 children from primary schools from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second year of the Obesity Action is not a coincidence that supports the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 pupils from 4th to 8th grade have been involved in the project.
Proper nutrition and sufficient movement in the family is one of the determining factors, which causes a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or even obese children.
“Only half of those surveyed, for example, said they ate breakfast-breakfast-lunch-dinner five times a day, which is one of the basic prerequisites for proper nutrition,” says one of the survey results.
Without breakfast and evening cessation
Experts note that for healthy development there are also important relative details, including, for example, the regular time of family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone has their own breakfast.
And the worst was the finding that in a tenth of the households do not have breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in the families of obese children, unhealthy french fries are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonade (70 percent) every day.
Although more than 40 percent of children surveyed regularly exercise, the result was less than half - 15 percent for their parents.
Set up your own diet.
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to make their own dietary options according to their own taste and opinion.
"The nutritional preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy nutrition."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of mellow, masturbating and sweet dishes.
“The great popularity of sweet lemonade is particularly alarming,” the study’s final report states.
For lunch as the main meal, pasta won just over poultry.
The children, however, practically did not want peanuts at all and low is the popularity of fish and mid-vegetable dishes.
An Inclination to Health
At the same time, the study showed that children are willing to adjust their eating habits if they get the right information.
"In a control group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the end of the Obesity education lecture, there was a significant shift in preferences towards healthy eating principles in a number of cases," the results of the project said.
This was significant, for example, in the case of sweet lemonades, where more children would begin to prefer ordinary water.
Children also more often turned on poultry and fish in the questionnaire as the main meal of the day and would limit sweet foods and snacks.
