Replacing analog signals with digital signals is one of the most important changes the world has experienced in recent years.
The Supreme State Court (SCJN) has rejected a constitutional lawsuit filed by the Senate and the House of Representatives against the presidential decree, which seeks to speed up the so-called "disabling of analog signals" and implement it in 2015 instead of in 2021.
