There was a relocation of the seized house, in which gigantic parties were held
Intruders seized 11 out of 13 apartments in a building in Balmes, 51
12 occupants left the house yesterday at noon without protesting
All evidence suggests that the nightmare that the neighbors of number 51 on Balmes Street have been through is finally over.
Twelve people left the building at noon yesterday voluntarily, where they lived illegally, and where they organized gigantic parties that woke the neighbors, leaving the building by court order and without having to interfere with the police.
At the end of the operation, the lock on the door was replaced to prevent a recurrence of the situation.
"From now on, the entrance will be guarded," the manager said.
The occupants, who took 11 of the 13 apartments in the building - the rest are inhabited - took away all electrical and partly water equipment, in addition to painting the walls and leaving behind all kinds of waste, especially cans after alcoholic beverages.
In the first three apartments there were huge parties that lasted up to two days and woke up the other tenants.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that during the time the building was occupied, sales fell by 80%.
The owner of the discotheque emphasizes that the occupants of the building made it unfair competition, because they sold drinks for 3 euros, while the discotheque costs 10 euros.
In addition, the owner of the entertainment company had to respond to complaints from neighbors about noise. However, the problems were not caused by the visitors of the discotheques, but by the residents of the rented house and especially those who attended the festivities held here.
The owner of the discotheque explained that the problems were so great that they even agreed with the owner of the building and for nine months she has been forgiving her rent.
The city police have also confirmed that they have received more complaints from neighbours over the past few weeks about the situation.
Alberto Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez D<0xC3><0xAD>az, the chairman of the city group of the PP People's Party at the town hall, last week called for "the building to be immediately evacuated and thus end with the problems of civil coexistence suffered by the neighbours and with the destruction of the area".
The president of the people explained that only one floor was taken last summer, but in recent months, the occupants got to all the floors of the building and almost all the apartments, and in one of them there were even thefts.
In this regard, he added that "it is necessary to end impunity and to be consistent when it comes to acts against civil liability that occurred in the building".
Yesterday, the city police also cleared the building in Nou Barris.
At 15:30 p.m., police arrived at building 35 on Mont-ral Street after being called by neighbors who saw four people entering the building.
All four of them were immediately arrested.
